race.comment: Tough contest with plenty of chances. WATOTO (5) is holding his form and due for a change of luck. Went back from the awkward gate and returned solid closing splits when fourth over this journey at Gundagai. Gets a better set-up for this with the blinkers coming off. No surprise to see him return to winning form. DOUBTFREE (14) unlucky not to have a few more wins on his CV and stretches out to his right distance range today. Strong through the line when third over 1180m at Gundagai. Well placed from the draw and shapes as the value in the race. HIGH COUNTRY STAR (3) has looked good in his two career starts, most recently scoring by 1.5 lengths over 1400m at this track. Has claims. DOORALONG (2) lightly raced gelding who was beaten 2.25 lengths into second last start over 1175m at this track. Can feature.
